<div class="ten columns">
  <div class="ten columns"><h3>Updating <%= @subscription.description %></h3></div>
  <div class="five columns">
    <div class="shimmed">
      <h4>Customize Your Alert</h4>
      <p>Now you have real ultimate power!  You can customize your very own text shredder alert.  You could use up your 140 charachters by telling yourself just how rad you are, or you can use the following widgets to add some real info:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>{{new_snow}}</li>
        <li>{{base_depth}}</li>
        <li>{{mid_depth}}</li>
        <li>{{base_temp}}</li>
        <li>{{mid_temp}}</li>
        <li>{{summit_temp}}</li>
        <li>{{report_time}}</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="four columns">
    <div class="shimmed">
    <%= form_for(@subscription, :as => 'subscription') do |f| %>
      <%= f.label :inches, 'Freshies Threshold:' %>
      <%= f.select :inches, (2..12).collect{|i| ["#{i} or more inches",i]}, {:include_blank => false, :value => @subscription.inches} %>
      <%= f.label :message, 'Text Message:' %>
      <%= f.text_area :message, { :cols => 0, :rows => 0, :style => '', :class => 'message' } %>
      <span class="countdown"></span>
      <%= f.submit 'Update' %>
      <a class="button" id="preview">Update Preview</a>
    <% end %>

    <h5>Alert Preview</h5>
    <div id="preview-window"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="sidebar five columns offset-by-one">
  <div class="highlight shimmed">
  <h3>Want to Bail?</h3>
  <p>If you want to remove this alert, just click this crazy large button down below. Keep in mind, there is no way to add a new alert right now... so check yoself before you wreck yoself.</p>
  <%=link_to "Delete Subscription?",subscription_path(@subscription.id), :method => :delete, :class => "danger", :confirm => "Are you sure ?"%>
  </div>
</div>
